statement alone is sufficient.

00:07:06.750 --> 00:07:10.500
D. Both statement one and
statement two together are not

00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:11.755
sufficient to answer the question.

00:07:12.630 --> 00:07:15.390
Understand the question
before moving to explanation.

00:07:15.810 --> 00:07:17.609
All right, let's break it down.

00:07:17.940 --> 00:07:20.909
Statement one says the
sum of digits is nine.

00:07:21.210 --> 00:07:21.599
Hmm.

00:07:21.810 --> 00:07:26.130
So it could be 18, 27, 36, 45.

00:07:26.280 --> 00:07:27.659
Lots of possibilities.

00:07:27.989 --> 00:07:30.510
So statement one alone is not sufficient.

00:07:31.260 --> 00:07:33.539
Now let's look at statement two alone.

00:07:33.900 --> 00:07:36.330
The 10 digit is twice the units digit.

00:07:36.750 --> 00:07:41.340
This could mean 21, 42, 63, or 84.

00:07:41.609 --> 00:07:43.320
Again, too many choices.

00:07:43.680 --> 00:07:46.440
So statement two alone is not sufficient.

00:07:46.890 --> 00:07:50.340
But what happens when we
combine them from statement one?

00:07:50.460 --> 00:07:56.755
We have D plus U equals nine from
statement 2D equals to u. Let's substitute

00:07:57.145 --> 00:08:02.425
two u plus U equals nine, which means
three U equals nine, so U is three.

00:08:02.755 --> 00:08:04.975
If U is three, D must be six.

00:08:05.305 --> 00:08:06.835
The number is 63.

00:08:07.135 --> 00:08:11.455
We found a unique answer, so both
statements together are sufficient.

00:08:11.815 --> 00:08:17.995
The correct answer is C. Example
